{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"68d43216-d74e-446b-b5f7-f0c1b830ebff","content":"TUnit uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** natively, so you need `--treenode-filter` (not `--filter`). The tree node path is `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<test>`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThis matches all tests inside the `SmsNotificationTests` class regardless of assembly or namespace. You could also be fully explicit:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/TestProject/Contoso.Notifications.Tests/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d877cc76-8cbc-43d4-858c-de50c769bf17","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For MTP-based projects, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nFor TUnit with MTP, the class filter uses `--treenode-filter` with the syntax:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The filter syntax for MTP is `--treenode-filter`. The tree node filter pattern for TUnit follows a path-like structure.\n\nActually, for TUnit with MTP, the filter uses `--treenode-filter` with a pattern like `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*` to match all tests in the class.\n\n\nThe treenode filter format follows an assembly/namespace/class/test hierarchy, so I can filter by class name using the pattern `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests` or with wildcards like `/**/*SmsNotificationTests*` to be more flexible. Since this is TUnit v0.6.120 running on MTP, the correct approach is using the treenode filter syntax.","outputTokens":590,"requestId":"A02F:1FF93E:D7353F:FC99A7:69FE8EDD"},"id":"3a4c73b9-6367-4a59-92c3-446e067a7145","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:33:29.871Z","parentId":"87211501-7cfb-4673-bda5-cef9d64b7076"}
